-- BP, Capita Group, IG Group Holdings, Ryanair: U.K., Irish Equity Preview
-- Ben Martin
-- 2010-07-20T04:00:02Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/bp-capita-group-ig-group-holdings-ryanair-u-k-irish-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in U.K. and Irish
markets. Stock symbols are in parentheses and prices are from
the last market close.  
 The benchmark  FTSE 100 Index  fell 10.57, or 0.2 percent, to
5,148.28. The  FTSE All-Share Index  declined 0.2 percent and
Ireland’s  ISEQ Index  fell 1.2 percent.  
 BP Plc  (BP/ LN): Talks between BP and Apache Corp. on BP
selling half of its stake in Alaska’s Prudhoe Bay oil field have
resumed after stalling over the weekend, a person familiar with
the matter said. The shares declined 4.7 percent to 387.85
pence.  
 Capita Group Plc  (CPI LN): Capita Symonds, a unit of U.K.
consultant firm Capita Group, plans to develop a 150 million-
pound ($228 million) tidal technology test site in Wales. The
stock fell 1.1 percent to 740.5 pence.  
 IG Group Holdings Plc  (IGG LN): The owner of the IG Index
financial spread-betting brand is due to report full-year
earnings. The shares advanced 0.7 percent to 466.6 pence.  
 Ryanair Holdings Plc  (RYA ID): The airline is scheduled to
report first-quarter earnings. The stock fell 1.1 percent to
3.78 euros.  
